---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions | Synax AI"
  description="Review the terms and conditions for using the Synax AI platform and the Obsight forensic workbench."
>
  <!-- TERMS PAGE
			============================================= -->
  <section
    id="terms-page"
    class="gr--whitesmoke pb-80 inner-page-hero division"
  >
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-xl-10 terms-content">
          <h5>Terms and Conditions</h5>
          <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> [March 26, 2026]</p>
          <p style="color:#6b7280; font-size:0.9rem;">
            This document defines the legal terms governing access to Synax and
            Obsight. It establishes the scope, limitations, and responsibilities
            associated with use of the platform.
          </p>
          <p>
            These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern your access to and use
            of the Synax platform, including Obsight and any associated tools,
            products, or services (collectively, the "Service").
          </p>

          <h5>1. Acceptance of Terms</h5>
          <p>
            By accessing or using the Service, you acknowledge that you have
            read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do
            not agree, you must discontinue use immediately.
          </p>

          <h5>2. Scope of the Service</h5>
          <p>
            The Service is designed to provide structured access to publicly
            available company disclosures, filings, and financial information.
          </p>
          <p>
            Obsight processes and presents this information as structured
            observations, signals, and contextual data to assist users in their
            own analytical workflows.
          </p>

          <h5>3. No Investment Advice or Recommendation</h5>
          <p>
            The Service does not provide investment advice, financial advice, or
            recommendations of any kind.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nothing contained within the Service constitutes an offer,
            solicitation, or recommendation to buy, sell, or hold any security
            or financial instrument.
          </p>
          <p>
            All outputs are informational in nature and must not be relied upon
            as a substitute for independent judgment or professional advice.
          </p>

          <h5>4. User Responsibility and Independent Judgment</h5>
          <p>
            You are solely responsible for any interpretation, analysis, or
            conclusions derived from the Service.
          </p>
          <p>
            Any decisions made based on the Service are made at your own risk.
            You are expected to perform independent verification and due
            diligence before acting on any information.
          </p>

          <h5>5. Data Sources and Accuracy</h5>
          <p>
            The Service relies on publicly available data and automated
            processing systems. While reasonable efforts are made to maintain
            data integrity, Synax makes no representation or warranty regarding
            the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of any information
            provided.
          </p>
          <p>
            Data may contain inaccuracies, omissions, or delays, and users
            should independently verify all information before relying on it.
          </p>

          <h5>6. Beta and Evolving Product Disclaimer</h5>
          <p>
            The Service may be in an early-stage, experimental, or beta phase.
            Features, outputs, and system behavior may change without notice and
            may not be complete or fully reliable.
          </p>
          <p>
            Synax does not guarantee the availability, continuity, or
            performance of the Service.
          </p>

          <h5>7. Permitted Use</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the Service solely for lawful and professional purposes</li>
            <li>
              Do not misuse, reverse engineer, or attempt to disrupt the Service
            </li>
            <li>
              Do not rely exclusively on the Service for critical financial
              decisions
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h5>8. Third-Party Data and Dependencies</h5>
          <p>
            The Service may incorporate or reference third-party data sources.
            Synax does not control or guarantee the accuracy or availability of
            such data.
          </p>

          <h5>9. Limitation of Liability</h5>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, Synax shall not be liable
            for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or financial
            losses arising from the use of or reliance on the Service.
          </p>
          <p>
            This includes, without limitation, losses resulting from investment
            decisions, data inaccuracies, or service interruptions.
          </p>

          <h5>10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h5>
          <p>
            The Service is provided on an "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" basis
            without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied.
          </p>
          <p>
            Synax disclaims all warranties, including but not limited to fitness
            for a particular purpose, reliability, and uninterrupted
            availability.
          </p>

          <h5>11. Termination</h5>
          <p>
            Synax reserves the right to suspend or terminate access to the
            Service at its sole discretion, without prior notice, in the event
            of misuse or violation of these Terms.
          </p>

          <h5>12. Governing Law</h5>
          <p>
            These Terms shall be governed by and interpreted in accordance with
            the laws of India.
          </p>

          <h5>13. Updates to Terms</h5>
          <p>
            Synax may update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the
            Service after changes are published constitutes acceptance of the
            revised Terms.
          </p>

          <h5>14. Contact</h5>
          <p>For any questions regarding these Terms:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email: info@synax.ai</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- End row -->
    </div>
    <!-- End container -->
  </section>
  <!-- END TERMS PAGE -->
  <style>
    /* ===== TERMS PAGE STYLING ===== */

    #terms-page {
      padding: 80px 0;
      background: #fafafa;
    }

    /* Container width control */
    #terms-page .col-xl-10 {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    /* Headings */
    #terms-page h5 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    #terms-page h5 {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      color: #111827;
    }

    /* Paragraphs */
    #terms-page p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #4b5563;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    /* Lists */
    #terms-page ul {
      padding-left: 18px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    #terms-page li {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: #4b5563;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    /* Strong text */
    #terms-page strong {
      color: #111827;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* Subtle divider between sections */
    #terms-page h5 {
      border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      padding-top: 16px;
    }

    /* First section no border */
    #terms-page h5:first-of-type {
      border-top: none;
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    /* Links */
    #terms-page a {
      color: #2563eb;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    #terms-page a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* Small text (last updated) */
    #terms-page p strong {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* Responsive */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      #terms-page {
        padding: 50px 20px;
      }

      #terms-page h5 {
        font-size: 1.8rem;
      }

      #terms-page h5 {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
      }

      #terms-page p,
      #terms-page li {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
    }
    .terms-content {
      background: white;
      padding: 40px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    }
    #terms-page {
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
